From: Marek Szyprowski <m.szyprowski@samsung.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2020 20:47:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/11] rpi4: shorten a mapping for the DRAM

Remove the overlap between DRAM and device's IO area.

Signed-off-by: Marek Szyprowski <m.szyprowski@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: Sylwester Nawrocki <s.nawrocki@samsung.com>
Reviewed-by: Nicolas Saenz Julienne <nsaenzjulienne@suse.de>

Upstream-Status: Pending in upstream patch queue

Signed-off-by: Jason Wessel <jason.wessel@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-bcm283x/init.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-bcm283x/init.c b/arch/arm/mach-bcm283x/init.c
index 9966d6c833..42953561a7 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-bcm283x/init.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-bcm283x/init.c
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@ static struct mm_region bcm2711_mem_map[] = {
 	{
 		.virt = 0x00000000UL,
 		.phys = 0x00000000UL,
-		.size = 0xfe000000UL,
+		.size = 0xfc000000UL,
 		.attrs = PTE_BLOCK_MEMTYPE(MT_NORMAL) |
 			 PTE_BLOCK_INNER_SHARE
 	}, {
